  "prompt": "Do car manufacturers produce new models every year?",
  "response": "Car manufacturers typically release new models and updates to existing models on an annual basis, but this can vary widely depending on the manufacturer, the specific model, and market demand. \n\nSome key points about model production include:\n\n1. **Annual Updates**: Many manufacturers introduce annual updates or facelifts for their popular models, which may include minor changes to design, features, or technology.\n\n2. **Complete Redesigns**: Major redesigns or new model introductions often occur every few years, typically on a 3 to 7-year cycle, depending on the vehicle segment.\n\n3. **Special Editions**: Some brands may also celebrate milestones or specific events by releasing limited edition models or special variants.\n\n4. **Market Trends**: Manufacturers may choose to fast-track the development of certain models in response to market trends, competition, or technological advancements, such as electric and hybrid vehicles.\n\n5. **Regulations**: Changes in emissions or safety regulations can prompt manufacturers to update models more frequently to ensure compliance.\n\n6. **Global Variations**: Different markets may receive different models or variations of models, influenced by local preferences and regulations.\n\nIn summary, while there is a general trend of annual updates, the introduction of entirely new models tends to follow a longer cycle.",
